Action: string; Action performed by gateway on the HTTP request.
ApplicationIDs: array[int]; IDs of the applications that matched the HTTP request parameters.
ApplicationNames: array[string]; Names of the applications that matched the HTTP request parameters.
BlockedFileHash: string; Hash of the file blocked in the response, if any.
BlockedFileName: string; File name blocked in the request, if any.
BlockedFileReason: string; Reason file was blocked in the response, if any.
BlockedFileSize: int; File size(bytes) blocked in the response, if any.
BlockedFileType: string; File type blocked in the response eg. exe, bin, if any.
CategoryIDs: array[int]; IDs of the categories that matched the HTTP request parameters.
CategoryNames: array[string]; Names of the categories that matched the HTTP request parameters.
Datetime: int or string; The date and time the corresponding HTTP request was made.
DestinationIP: string; Destination ip of the request.
DestinationIPContinentCode: string; Continent code of the destination IP of the HTTP request (for example, 'NA').
DestinationIPCountryCode: string; Country code of the destination IP of the HTTP request (for example, 'US').
DestinationPort: int; Destination port of the request.
DeviceID: string; UUID of the device where the HTTP request originated from.
DeviceName: string; The name of the device where the HTTP request originated from (for example, 'Laptop MB810').
DownloadMatchedDlpProfileEntries: array[string]; List of matched DLP entries in the HTTP request.
DownloadMatchedDlpProfiles: array[string]; List of matched DLP profiles in the HTTP request.
DownloadedFileNames: array[string]; List of files downloaded in the HTTP request.
Email: string; Email used to authenticate the client.
FileInfo: object; Information about files detected within the HTTP request.
ForensicCopyStatus: string; Status of any associated forensic copies that may have been captured during the request.
HTTPHost: string; Content of the host header in the HTTP request.
HTTPStatusCode: int; HTTP status code gateway returned to the user. Zero if nothing was returned (for example, client disconnected).
HTTPVersion: string; Version name for the HTTP request.
IsIsolated: bool; If the requested was isolated with Cloudflare Browser Isolation or not.
PolicyID: string; The gateway policy UUID applied to the request, if any.
PolicyName: string; The name of the gateway policy applied to the request, if any.
PrivateAppAUD: string; The private app AUD, if any.
ProxyEndpoint: string: The proxy endpoint used on the HTTP request, if any.
Quarantined: bool; If the request content was quarantined.
RedirectTargetURI: string; Custom URI to which the user was redirected, if any.
Referer: string; Contents of the referer header in the HTTP request.
RegistrationID: string; The UUID of the device registration from which the HTTP request originated.
RequestID: string; Cloudflare request ID. This might be empty on bypass action.
SourceIP: string; Source ip of the request.
SourceIPContinentCode: string; Continent code of the source IP of the request (for example, 'NA').
SourceIPCountryCode: string; Country code of the source IP of the request (for example, 'US').
SourceInternalIP: string; Local LAN IP of the device. Only available when connected via a GRE/IPsec tunnel on-ramp.
SourcePort: int; Source port of the request.
UntrustedCertificateAction: string; Action taken when an untrusted origin certificate error occurs (for example, expired certificate, mismatched common name, invalid certificate chain, signed by non-public CA). One of none | block | error | passThrough.
UploadMatchedDlpProfileEntries: array[string]; List of matched DLP entries in the HTTP request.
UploadMatchedDlpProfiles: array[string]; List of matched DLP profiles in the HTTP request.
UploadedFileNames: array[string]; List of files uploaded in the HTTP request.
UserAgent: string; Contents of the user agent header in the HTTP request.
UserID: string; User identity where the HTTP request originated from.
VirtualNetworkID: string; The identifier of the virtual network the device was connected to, if any.
VirtualNetworkName: string; The name of the virtual network the device was connected to, if any.
